tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE liability_insurance_rates (
  client_id INT,
  policy_id INT,
  policy_start_date DATE,
  policy_end_date DATE,
  coverage_amount DECIMAL,
  premium_amount DECIMAL,
  claim_status VARCHAR(255)
);

CREATE TABLE liability_insurance_rates (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  insurance_provider_id INT,
  rate DECIMAL,
  effective_date DATE,
  expiration_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE market_trends (
  trend_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  trend_name VARCHAR(50),
  trend_description TEXT,
  trend_start_date DATE,
  trend_end_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE liability_insurance_rates (
  policy_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  policy_holder_name VARCHAR(255),
  policy_start_date DATE,
  policy_end_date DATE,
  coverage_amount DECIMAL(10, 2)
);

CREATE TABLE rate_adjustments (
  adjustment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  policy_id INT,
  trend_id INT,
  adjusted_rate DECIMAL(8, 4),
  adjustment_date DATE,
  FOREIGN KEY (policy_id) REFERENCES liability_insurance_rates(policy_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (trend_id) REFERENCES market_trends(trend_id)
);

CREATE TABLE liability_insurance_rates (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    insurance_company varchar(255),
    coverage_type varchar(255),
    rate DECIMAL(10, 2),
    effective_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE liability_insurance_rates (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    company_name VARCHAR(255),
    coverage_type VARCHAR(50),
    effective_date DATE,
    expiration_date DATE,
    rate DECIMAL(10, 2)
)

CREATE TABLE market_trends (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    trend_name VARCHAR(50),
    trend_description TEXT,
    trend_start_date DATE,
    trend_end_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE analysis_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    analysis_date DATE,
    analysis_details TEXT,
    analysis_result VARCHAR(100)
)

CREATE TABLE adjustment_history (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    adjustment_date DATE,
    adjustment_details TEXT,
    adjustment_reason VARCHAR(100)
)

CREATE TABLE user_feedback (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    feedback_date DATE,
    feedback_details TEXT,
    user_name VARCHAR(50)
)
